00:41:07,832 --> 00:41:09,767
- And…
- Oh, no, and what?

704
00:41:09,834 --> 00:41:12,837
- And? Tell us what happened.
- And? Did something happen?

705
00:41:12,903 --> 00:41:15,973
And today, we decided we're together.

706
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:16,974
- What?
- Congrats!

707
00:41:17,041 --> 00:41:19,109
- So that's what.
- We're together.

708
00:41:19,176 --> 00:41:20,845
Congratulations.

709
00:41:20,911 --> 00:41:23,380
- That's what I wanted to hear.
- That's great news.

710
00:41:23,447 --> 00:41:25,950
- We all want to celebrate.
- Look at you squirming!

711
00:41:26,016 --> 00:41:27,585
- We're friends!
- A toast!

712
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:29,487
- It's embarrassing.
- A toast?

713
00:41:31,355 --> 00:41:32,590
I'm happy for you.

714
00:41:32,656 --> 00:41:34,091
- Yeah.
- Yeah, I'm really happy.

715
00:41:36,427 --> 00:41:38,762
- Hey, wait a minute.
- Why are you crying?

716
00:41:38,829 --> 00:41:40,764
<i>Kazu has a high level of empathy.</i>

717
00:41:40,831 --> 00:41:42,933
<i>Because</i>
<i>he's been through a lot in his life.</i>

718
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:44,101
<i>You're right.</i>

719
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:46,370
- I'm thinking how happy I am for you.
- You okay?

720
00:41:46,437 --> 00:41:48,239
- Kazuyuki.
- Kazuyuki.

721
00:41:48,739 --> 00:41:51,242
- I'm just so glad for you both.
- Thank you.

722
00:41:51,308 --> 00:41:52,476
Congratulations.

723
00:41:52,543 --> 00:41:57,014
- This was so unexpected. Are you okay?
- I'm just so glad.

724
00:41:57,681 --> 00:42:00,918
Thanks, Kazuyuki. When you start
to cry, it always makes me tear up too.

725
00:42:00,985 --> 00:42:02,119
Don't mind me!

726
00:42:02,653 --> 00:42:05,055
It makes me happy that you care so deeply.

727
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:07,758
All I can say is I'm very happy.

728
00:42:07,825 --> 00:42:09,660
On anniversaries like this,

729
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:13,664
it's rare to actually
be celebrated on the day itself, right?

730
00:42:13,731 --> 00:42:15,866
- It's rare.
- This doesn't happen to me.

731
00:42:15,933 --> 00:42:18,536
- This is definitely a special day for me.
- <i>Is Jobu okay?</i>

732
00:42:18,602 --> 00:42:20,004
<i>Is Jobu okay?</i>

733
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:22,873
<i>- His emotions… Oh, is he okay?</i>
- <i>Oh, he froze up.</i>

734
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:30,981
What color do you want?

735
00:42:31,048 --> 00:42:32,883
- Draw a heart in the center.
- Mmm.

736
00:42:32,950 --> 00:42:34,418
- Use the same color.
- Good idea.

737
00:42:34,485 --> 00:42:35,719
- You like that?
- Yeah.

738
00:42:37,087 --> 00:42:38,188
You do it.

739
00:42:38,756 --> 00:42:40,558
- You sure I can do it?
- Yeah.

740
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:42,459
This is embarrassing.

741
00:42:43,427 --> 00:42:44,261
Great.

742
00:42:45,529 --> 00:42:47,631
We've changed.
We changed little by little.

743
00:42:47,698 --> 00:42:49,300
- We did.
- This was the first time?

744
00:42:49,366 --> 00:42:51,835
Our very first time. The day I asked you.

745
00:42:52,937 --> 00:42:55,973
- In the end, I asked you out.
- You did. Thank you.

746
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:57,274
Thank you too.

747
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:03,847
Mmm…

748
00:43:04,615 --> 00:43:05,950
Oh, thanks.

749
00:43:09,887 --> 00:43:11,255
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

750
00:43:13,791 --> 00:43:16,794
- Are we allowed?
- I don't know. I think it's okay today.

751
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:20,798
- Goodnight. See you tomorrow.
- <i>They don't want to leave.</i>

752
00:43:20,864 --> 00:43:22,132
- <i>But have to</i>.
- <i>Separate.</i>

753
00:43:22,199 --> 00:43:24,568
<i>- The day they get together!</i>
- <i>They'll live together.</i>

754
00:43:24,635 --> 00:43:26,937
- <i>Yeah, but…</i>
- <i>Yeah, but this is nice too.</i>

755
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:31,709
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

756
00:43:33,677 --> 00:43:35,446
<i>Aaah!</i>

757
00:43:35,512 --> 00:43:37,214
<i>And the rooms are so far apart.</i>

758
00:43:37,281 --> 00:43:40,884
<i>They didn't close the door</i>
<i>for a while either. Oh, this is nice.</i>

759
00:43:42,386 --> 00:43:44,088
Hey, Hiroya isn't here.

760
00:43:44,655 --> 00:43:47,291
- It's hard to get everyone together.
- Right. It's like…

761
00:43:47,358 --> 00:43:48,759
I guess you're right.

762
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:50,060
But I'm glad.

763
00:43:50,828 --> 00:43:52,429
- Ryuki is back.
- Welcome back.

764
00:43:52,496 --> 00:43:54,431
- It's been two or three days.
- Are you okay?

765
00:43:54,498 --> 00:43:56,567
- How are you feeling?
- I'm okay. I'm good.

766
00:43:57,668 --> 00:43:58,669
Well…

767
00:44:00,437 --> 00:44:01,872
We're officially together.

768
00:44:01,939 --> 00:44:03,874
What, already?

769
00:44:03,941 --> 00:44:06,043
- That was fast.
- That was fast!

770
00:44:06,677 --> 00:44:08,979
This isn't the kind of progress
I'm used to.

771
00:44:09,046 --> 00:44:10,347
There's no such thing.

772
00:44:10,414 --> 00:44:12,516
- It happened yesterday.
- Wow.

773
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:16,120
- That's why today we are celebrating.
- That's why we're celebrating.

774
00:44:16,186 --> 00:44:18,222
- All day.
- We'll celebrate tonight.

775
00:44:18,288 --> 00:44:19,623
Sounds good.

776
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:26,463
- Oh? Huh?
- Huh? Huh?

777
00:44:26,530 --> 00:44:28,165
- What's going on?
- Huh?

778
00:44:28,232 --> 00:44:29,366
Where are you going?

779
00:44:29,433 --> 00:44:31,368
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

780
00:44:31,869 --> 00:44:34,138
- Just for a while…
- That startled me.

781
00:44:34,204 --> 00:44:36,140
I'm leaving the Green Room. Yeah.

782
00:44:36,206 --> 00:44:39,243
- You're leaving today?
- For a short while? You're coming back.

783
00:44:39,309 --> 00:44:40,944
I'm going on a business trip abroad.

784
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:42,112
- Really?
- Is that so?

785
00:44:42,179 --> 00:44:44,782
The project I've been working on
so hard the past few years

786
00:44:44,848 --> 00:44:45,916
is finally coming together.

787
00:44:45,983 --> 00:44:46,850
Mmm.

788
00:44:46,917 --> 00:44:49,653
So I want to be there
for that final moment. Yeah.

789
00:44:50,154 --> 00:44:52,156
I won't be back right away.

790
00:44:52,656 --> 00:44:56,360
So, while I'm gone,
to remind you of my time here so far…

791
00:44:56,427 --> 00:44:58,929
- You printed these for us?
- Wow, there are so many!

792
00:44:58,996 --> 00:45:01,398
- These are really nice.
- Photo stands? Cute!

793
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:03,333
- How cute.
- I made photo stands.

794
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:05,703
- Put them up somewhere and add your photo.
- Awesome.

795
00:45:05,769 --> 00:45:07,538
- These are great.
- So nice of you.

796
00:45:07,604 --> 00:45:09,606
- Thanks guys.
- Thanks.

797
00:45:10,207 --> 00:45:12,109
- I've gotta go.
- See you soon.

798
00:45:12,176 --> 00:45:14,311
- Take care of yourself.
- Good luck.

799
00:45:15,946 --> 00:45:18,115
- Bye! See you soon.
- We'll miss you.

800
00:45:18,182 --> 00:45:20,584
- See you soon!
- Take care!

801
00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:21,752
See you!

802
00:45:23,654 --> 00:45:25,956
- <i>How long is the trip?</i>
- <i>He's coming back?</i>

803
00:45:26,023 --> 00:45:27,925
<i>- He's not leaving?</i>
- <i>I think it's a week?</i>

804
00:45:27,991 --> 00:45:28,826
Honestly?

805
00:45:29,727 --> 00:45:31,428
I have one less rival.

806
00:45:31,495 --> 00:45:34,064
- <i>Well, that's true.</i>
- <i>No wonder Bomi's laughing.</i>

807
00:45:34,131 --> 00:45:35,999
I mean, I shouldn't be
thinking this way,

808
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:40,270
but I feel like I don't have
to rush the situation anymore,

809
00:45:40,337 --> 00:45:42,806
and I can take my time talking to Huwei.

810
00:45:44,241 --> 00:45:47,311
<i>Well, I did have</i>
<i>a rather sad experience in Niseko,</i>

811
00:45:47,377 --> 00:45:50,781
<i>but if it's not too late</i>
<i>when I get back to the Green Room</i>…

812
00:45:50,848 --> 00:45:51,915
TANCHO KUSHIRO AIRPORT

813
00:45:51,982 --> 00:45:55,586
<i>…I want to focus my efforts</i>
<i>on Huwei once again.</i>

814
00:45:55,652 --> 00:45:57,054
<i>He wants to try again?</i>

815
00:46:00,657 --> 00:46:02,159
<i>Someone new is here.</i>

816
00:46:04,928 --> 00:46:06,730
<i>Ohh!</i>

817
00:46:06,797 --> 00:46:08,265
<i>What? Is that Taeheon?</i>

818
00:46:08,332 --> 00:46:10,768
<i>Is that Taeheon?</i>

819
00:46:10,834 --> 00:46:12,936
- What?
- Why? What is he doing here?

820
00:46:13,003 --> 00:46:14,772
- This is crazy!
- What's going on in this show?

821
00:46:14,838 --> 00:46:17,708
- Taeheon!
- Taeheon's coming back?
